Structure. Body 1.3–1.5 times as long as wide. Antenna 9-segmented, often division of segment 8 and 9 incomplete, 1.8–2.2 times as long as forewing pad. Marginal setae on forewing pad weakly capitate, particularly the longer ones, long and medium long, the longer setae mostly longer than distance between bases of adjacent setae; setae on dorsum of wing pads pointed (
Fig. 169
). Circumanal ring large, strongly indented anteriorly (
Fig. 172
).

Measurements (in mm) and ratios (
7 immatures
). Body length 1.42–1.64, antenna length 1.04–1.22.
